1. There was a posttest step and follow-up stage in the study.
2. The study had an experimental group and a control group.
3. The mean scores of spiritual wellbeing were measured in the study.
4. The religious dimension of spiritual wellbeing was measured in the study.
5. The existential aspect of spiritual wellbeing was measured in the study.
6. In the posttest step and follow-up stage, the mean scores of spiritual wellbeing in the experimental group were higher than in the control group.
7. In the posttest step and follow-up stage, the mean scores of the religious dimension of spiritual wellbeing in the experimental group were higher than in the control group.
8. In the posttest step and follow-up stage, the mean scores of the existential aspect of spiritual wellbeing in the experimental group were higher than in the control group.
9. The differences in mean scores of spiritual wellbeing, the religious dimension, and the existential aspect of spiritual wellbeing between the experimental and control groups were statistically significant (P < 0.001).
